<plot>An entry in Columbia's audience-participation singalongs where 'Don Baker (IX)' (qv), playing the organ, and 'The Song Spinners' (qv), singing the songs, display their wares on four songs, until the Bouncing Ball comes alive and leads the theatre patrons in singing the fifth song. The title has nothing to do with sexual preference...it is referring to 'happy' songs.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?210924</url></doc>
